'''Dudelange communal council''' ({{lang-fr|Conseil communal de Dudelange}}; [[Luxembourgish]]: ''Diddelenger Gemengerot'') is the [[Local government|local council]] for the [[Communes of Luxembourg|commune]] of ''[[Dudelange]]'' (Luxem-bourgish: ''Diddeleng''), in southern [[Luxembourg]].
It consists of seventeen members, elected every six years by [[proportional representation]].<ref name="Conseil communal">{{cite web|url=http://www.dudelange.lu/Vie+politique/Conseil+communal.html |title=Conseil communal |accessdate=2007-09-06 |date= |publisher=Ville de Dudelange |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927201510/http://www.dudelange.lu/Vie+politique/Conseil+communal.html |archivedate=2007-09-27 |language=fr |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> The last elections were held on 9 October 2005, and resulted in a victory for the [[Luxembourg Socialist Workers' Party]] (LSAP). In the ''[[Collège échevinal (Luxembourg)|collège échevinal]]'' (Luxembourgish: ''Schäfferot''; English: ''Board of Aldermen''), the LSAP rules outright, under the leadership of [[Mayor of Dudelange|mayor]] [[Alex Bodry]].<ref name="Conseil communal" />
